# TAMS — Official Documentation Standards

Applies to all files under `docs/official/`. Follow these rules whenever creating or editing official project documentation.

## Language and Tone

- Write all content in **English** (consistent with `general.mdc`).
- Use clear, formal technical prose suitable for formal software documentation.
- Do **not** copy template guidance text into output documents: no `InfoBlue` notes, `_Usage note_`, or `_[Provide...]_` placeholders.

## Project Identity

- Full name: **TAMS — Transcript Analysis and Graduation Control System**
- Short name: **TAMS**
- Use the full name on document title pages; use TAMS in body text after first mention.

## Source Hierarchy

Verify claims against these sources before writing. Prefer code and existing docs over inference.

| Priority | Source | Use for |
|----------|--------|---------|
| 1 | `services/`, `frontend/`, `infrastructure/` | Implemented behavior, APIs, schemas |
| 2 | `docs/architecture.md` | System design, services, data flow, security |
| 3 | `docs/graduation-rules-v2-architecture.md` | Graduation rule engine logic |
| 3 | `docs/category-course-cohort-bounds.md` | Category-course enrollment cohort bounds (year + GUZ/BAHAR term) |
| 4 | `README.md`, `docs/todo.md` | Scope, MVP features, completion status |
| 5 | `docs/production-deployment.md`, `docs/https-migration-guide.md` | Operational and deployment requirements |
| 6 | `docs/templates/*.md` | Section structure only — not content |

If a requirement or feature cannot be verified, mark it **TBD** or state the assumption explicitly under an Assumptions subsection.

## Cross-Reference IDs

Use consistent identifiers across all official documents:

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Functional requirement | `FR-<DOMAIN>-<NNN>` | `FR-AUTH-001` |
| Business rule | `BR-<DOMAIN>-<NNN>` | `BR-GRAD-001`, `BR-COHORT-001` |
| Use case | `UC-<DOMAIN>-<NNN>` | `UC-TEACH-002` |
| Architectural decision | `AD-<NNN>` | `AD-003` |

Link related items across Vision, SRS, Architecture Notebook, and Use Cases (e.g., a Vision need maps to `FR-*` entries and `UC-*` files).

## Required End Sections

Every official document must end with these two sections (in order):

### Traceability Table

| Section | Source | Author | Date |
|---------|--------|--------|------|
| _section name_ | _file path, API route, or commit_ | _person or agent_ | _YYYY-MM-DD_ |

One row per major section filled in the document.

### Prompts

List every Generative AI prompt used to produce or revise the document. Include a link to the full conversation when available. For Use Cases, place Prompts under an **APPENDIX** heading instead.

## What Not to Include

- Template instructional text or Word-specific formatting notes
- Unimplemented features presented as delivered (check `docs/todo.md`)
- Secrets, real credentials, or environment-specific values from `.env` files
